1
00:01:20,839 --> 00:01:21,400
Gu Tiancheng!

2
00:01:22,199 --> 00:01:23,000
Look at me if you can hear me.

3
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:24,599
Gu Tiancheng!

4
00:01:31,879 --> 00:01:32,519
Prepare for resuscitation.

5
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:55,839
Hello, Yaoyao.

6
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,279
Jiaqi.

7
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,360
Brother Du, he...

8
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:16,160
Jiaqi.

9
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:16,720
Look.

10
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,759
Isn't this

11
00:02:17,759 --> 00:02:19,080
the kind of house you like best?

12
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:21,960
A proposal gift?

13
00:02:22,279 --> 00:02:22,720
Yeah.

14
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,240
I spent a long time picking this out.

15
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:26,520
Come here.

16
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:27,000
Anything from you,

17
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:27,720
Put it on, baby.

18
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:28,320
I love it all.

19
00:02:43,199 --> 00:02:44,559
You've been in my life

20
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,199
for twenty years.

21
00:02:47,279 --> 00:02:47,919
You,

22
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:48,919
me,

23
00:02:49,399 --> 00:02:50,080
Ziang,

24
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,039
and Yaoyao.

25
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,080
We've gone through

26
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,559
our childhood and youth together.

27
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:55,919
Happiness,

28
00:02:56,839 --> 00:02:57,399
pain,

29
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,360
we've experienced it all together.

30
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:02,759
I thought our future would be ordinary,

31
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,800
but I never imagined

32
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,600
you'd be absent from the rest of my life.

33
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:10,320
Du Zheng,

34
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,160
how could you bear to leave me behind?

35
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:17,720
I'm leaving now.

36
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:21,720
I'll come visit you often.

37
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,960
My life was almost entirely gray.

38
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,639
It didn't allow me to believe in those things.

39
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,399
All I could do

40
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,800
was, before my heart stopped beating,

41
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,000
to constantly calculate and prepare.

42
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:45,639
However,

43
00:03:46,399 --> 00:03:47,600
on that very night,

44
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:50,759
fate's joke

45
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:52,839
began.

46
00:03:58,679 --> 00:03:59,479
Tiancheng,

47
00:04:02,119 --> 00:04:03,360
you're really lucky.

48
00:04:04,399 --> 00:04:05,399
You just happened to find

49
00:04:05,559 --> 00:04:07,440
a donor whose heart matches yours.

50
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:08,679
You really are

51
00:04:08,759 --> 00:04:10,119
blessed after surviving a great disaster.

52
00:04:11,119 --> 00:04:11,880
Tell me,

53
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,279
what good deeds did you do in your past life?

54
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,559
Dr. Duan,

55
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,559
thank you for taking care of me lately.

56
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:24,040
Wait,

57
00:04:24,519 --> 00:04:25,480
you... you... you...

58
00:04:26,119 --> 00:04:27,880
Are you possessed by something?

59
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:31,880
Move aside.

60
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,720
You're blocking the light.

61
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:46,320
That guy surnamed Cui

62
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,440
actually dared to betray me.

63
00:04:49,799 --> 00:04:50,640
He's now transferred

64
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,359
all his shares to Rosenmoss Company.

65
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,920
Rosenmoss Company

66
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,760
has become our company's largest creditor.

67
00:04:56,799 --> 00:04:58,799
They probably heard Gu Tiancheng's surgery was successful,

68
00:04:59,559 --> 00:05:00,559
so these shareholders

69
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:01,519
are panicking.

70
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,040
Our biggest problem

71
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,559
is resolving this month's

72
00:05:04,559 --> 00:05:06,320
debt interest and principal.

73
00:05:06,519 --> 00:05:07,200
Otherwise,

74
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:09,239
we'll have to go bankrupt.

75
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:10,640
Are you kidding me?

76
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:12,399
As long as I, Gu Rongchen, am here,

77
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:13,760
Feimanchi

78
00:05:14,239 --> 00:05:15,040
will absolutely not go bankrupt.

79
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:18,519
Tell me,

80
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:21,200
what kind of dumb luck do you have?

81
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,320
A one percent chance,

82
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:24,760
and it actually happened to you.

83
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,880
To be honest with you,

84
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:28,160
I

85
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,559
even had the wreaths ready for you.

86
00:05:30,799 --> 00:05:33,040
Like those big paper houses to burn,

87
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:35,279
I even prepared over eighty maids for you.

88
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:35,959
And also...

89
00:05:36,079 --> 00:05:36,880
Are you tired of living?

90
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:38,799
No, the doctor said

91
00:05:39,239 --> 00:05:40,399
that during this period,

92
00:05:40,519 --> 00:05:42,079
your emotions shouldn't fluctuate too much.

93
00:05:42,559 --> 00:05:43,040
By the way,

94
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,640
there's something.

95
00:05:43,799 --> 00:05:44,839
Did Dr. Duan remind you?

96
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:48,119
Remind me of what?

97
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,559
If I can't control

98
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:52,359
my hands and feet lately

99
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,279
and start hitting people randomly,

100
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:54,519
it's a normal post-op reaction.

101
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:55,720
Just bear with it.

102
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,279
You don't look like you just had surgery.

103
00:05:58,279 --> 00:05:59,239
You're so strong.

104
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:01,760
Fine.

105
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:02,920
Whenever you want to hit me in the future,

106
00:06:03,239 --> 00:06:04,320
I'll be ready anytime.

107
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,839
But seriously,

108
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,880
you just came back from death's door.

109
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:18,559
You must take care of your health from now on.

110
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:20,880
At the very least, you have to do justice to this heart.

111
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,799
Alright, stop nagging.

112
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,760
You sound like a woman.

113
00:06:32,359 --> 00:06:32,880
Hello.

114
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:33,799
This is Lin Jiaqi.

115
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,160
Where are you?

116
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,799
What are you thinking about?

117
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,040
I had a really weird dream.

118
00:07:11,959 --> 00:07:12,640
Weird?

119
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,119
How weird?

120
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,480
I dreamt of a woman.

121
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,519
She kept crying on my chest.

122
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,640
I wanted to see what she looked like,

123
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:24,519
but I couldn't see her face.

124
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,920
She was also wearing a hair clip.

125
00:07:30,119 --> 00:07:30,600
So, this...

126
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:32,399
woman with the hair clip,

127
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,760
she didn't do anything to you, did she?

128
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,119
Why do you talk so much?

129
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,640
It's all here.

130
00:07:43,799 --> 00:07:45,760
You never used to eat snacks before.

131
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,359
How come after the surgery,

132
00:07:47,559 --> 00:07:48,359
you're into this stuff?

133
00:07:50,239 --> 00:07:50,959
I don't know.

134
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,799
Probably just bored in the hospital.

135
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,839
From now on,

136
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:58,200
prepare some lollipops for me every day.

137
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,440
Alright.

138
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,160
Go ask the doctor when I can be discharged.

139
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,119
What are you waiting for?

140
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,600
I'll go ask right now.

141
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,119
Hurry up.

142
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:06,640
Wait for me.

143
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,559
Hurry up.

144
00:08:08,559 --> 00:08:09,119
Okay.

145
00:08:10,799 --> 00:08:11,519
Excuse me.

146
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,799
The hospital just called me.

147
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:14,679
They said

148
00:08:14,679 --> 00:08:15,720
someone found a

149
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,160
women's hair clip.

150
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,760
Okay, let me show you.

151
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:33,039
I was wondering why you looked so familiar.

152
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,400
Isn't this the traitor Lin's daughter?

153
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,479
Mr. Gu.

154
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,200
You're looking well.

155
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,960
I almost kicked the bucket because of you.

156
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:44,719
Did you know that?

157
00:08:46,039 --> 00:08:46,520
However,

158
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,440
heaven has eyes.

159
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,479
Not only did I not kick the bucket,

160
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:51,760
but I can also live for many more years.

161
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,479
I heard.

162
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,400
Congratulations.

163
00:08:55,719 --> 00:08:56,239
No way.

164
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:57,640
You came all the way here

165
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,880
just to say congratulations to me?

166
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,239
I bet you and Gu Rongchen

167
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,200
were really hoping that I

168
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,359
wouldn't make it off the operating table.

169
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,200
Right?

170
00:09:07,119 --> 00:09:07,960
I have something urgent to do.

171
00:09:08,239 --> 00:09:09,000
Let's talk later.

172
00:09:09,239 --> 00:09:09,760
Excuse me.

173
00:09:10,159 --> 00:09:10,640
Wait.

174
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:13,200
You want to leave before I'm done talking?

175
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,719
I really have something urgent.

176
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:20,679
What's with that attitude?

177
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:32,479
What's wrong?

178
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,640
My heart suddenly hurts so much.

179
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,119
Rest for a bit, rest for a bit.

180
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,880
I told you not to get so agitated.

181
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,320
Who's agitated?

182
00:09:39,599 --> 00:09:40,760
Okay, okay, you're not agitated.

183
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:41,520
Come, come, come.

184
00:09:41,599 --> 00:09:42,440
Have some candy, have some candy.

185
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:42,840
Eat it.

186
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:45,760
Calm down, calm down.

187
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,000
It's okay.

188
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,640
It's okay.

189
00:09:54,599 --> 00:09:55,359
Thank you.

190
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,119
I thought I couldn't find it.

191
00:09:58,119 --> 00:09:59,239
Seeing how anxious you were,

192
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:00,559
it must be

193
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,840
very important to you.

194
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,599
Mr. Gu.

195
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:09,440
Secretary Lin.

196
00:10:10,039 --> 00:10:11,640
Don't you still owe me an explanation?

197
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:12,719
I'm sorry.

198
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:13,520
That's it?

199
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,599
I, Gu Tiancheng,

200
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,239
never accept apologies.

201
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,320
A real apology

202
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,840
comes with a price.

203
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,080
What price?

204
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,200
As long as you sell Feimanchi's secrets to me,

205
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,440
we'll be even.

206
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:33,080
As long as I'm still part of Feimanchi,

207
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,359
as long as I'm still the chairman's secretary,

208
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,400
I can't do that.

209
00:10:37,599 --> 00:10:38,400
So loyal.

210
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,719
It's not about loyalty.

211
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,280
It's the basic duty of a secretary.

212
00:10:48,239 --> 00:10:48,719
Fine.

213
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,760
Since you're so loyal to Gu Rongchen,

214
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:52,760
when I send him to prison,

215
00:10:53,599 --> 00:10:55,599
I'll send you in with him to keep him company.

216
00:10:57,479 --> 00:10:57,840
Oh, right.

217
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,479
And that scoundrel boyfriend of yours.

218
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,440
I haven't forgotten.

219
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,599
My score with him isn't settled yet.

220
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:05,919
When the time comes,

221
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,799
I'll send him in too,

222
00:11:08,159 --> 00:11:09,400
to keep you guys company.

223
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,679
I've never seen anyone like you.

224
00:11:13,159 --> 00:11:14,320
You went to death's door

225
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,479
and barely got your life back,

226
00:11:16,479 --> 00:11:17,559
yet you haven't changed at all.

227
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,080
Everyone is right.

228
00:11:19,799 --> 00:11:21,719
You are an absolute scumbag.

229
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,200
Jerk.

230
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:26,919
Lin Jiaqi.

231
00:11:27,599 --> 00:11:28,359
Just you wait.

232
00:11:37,679 --> 00:11:39,359
Let's have a proper talk.

233
00:11:40,679 --> 00:11:42,840
From now on, we are a team.

234
00:11:44,039 --> 00:11:45,960
If you want to go against me,

235
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:48,719
it won't end well for you.

236
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:52,960
Do you hear me?

237
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,640
I'm talking to you.

238
00:11:54,599 --> 00:11:55,679
You'd better behave yourself.

239
00:11:56,479 --> 00:11:57,200
Otherwise,

240
00:11:57,719 --> 00:11:59,159
I'll rip you out.

241
00:12:04,039 --> 00:12:04,479
No.

242
00:12:04,479 --> 00:12:05,679
Could it be that the surgery wasn't successful?

243
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,719
Could Dr. Duan be lying to me?

244
00:12:09,119 --> 00:12:10,559
Is this all an illusion he created to trick me?

245
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:14,359
Thank you.

246
00:12:15,599 --> 00:12:17,359
Is the company not too busy today?

247
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:18,719
How do you have time to treat me to a meal?

248
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,159
Could company matters

249
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,400
be more important than you?

250
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:22,760
By the way,

251
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,039
I found this.

252
00:12:29,799 --> 00:12:30,799
I thought it was lost,

253
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,000
but I unexpectedly got it back.

254
00:12:32,799 --> 00:12:33,640
It's as if Du Zheng

255
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,320
is trying to tell me something.

256
00:12:36,119 --> 00:12:36,679
Nonsense.

257
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:38,840
Since when did you become so superstitious?

258
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:39,799
I'm not being superstitious.

259
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:40,520
I'm telling the truth.

260
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,119
Don't you think it's quite a coincidence?

261
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:44,599
So many coincidences happen in the world every day.

262
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,000
Stop overthinking.

263
00:12:47,599 --> 00:12:48,880
Maybe I've just been too tired lately.

264
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,280
I've been acting paranoid all day.

265
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:52,599
Jiaqi,

266
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,200
you need to accept reality as soon as possible.

267
00:12:55,239 --> 00:12:56,280
We used to be three people,

268
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,520
but now it's just the two of us.

269
00:12:59,599 --> 00:13:00,799
Didn't Du Zheng say it before?

270
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:02,719
Happiness will pass,

271
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:04,719
and sorrow will pass too.

272
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,520
I believe what he said.

273
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:07,679
So,

274
00:13:08,679 --> 00:13:09,359
you don't need to worry.

275
00:13:09,599 --> 00:13:10,719
But if anything happens to you,

276
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,719
you must let me know immediately.

277
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,039
No matter what I'm doing,

278
00:13:14,679 --> 00:13:16,000
I'll rush over to help you right away.

279
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:17,320
Thank you.

280
00:13:20,359 --> 00:13:21,440
Oh, my goodness.

281
00:13:21,479 --> 00:13:22,679
What are you doing here?

282
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,520
Do you know how hard it was to find you?

283
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,640
Dr. Duan specifically said

284
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,440
you shouldn't be exerting yourself.

285
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,200
You shouldn't be running around.

286
00:13:31,719 --> 00:13:32,039
I mean,

287
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:33,039
can you save me some worry?

288
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,520
Just save me some worry for once.

289
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,520
Just get to the point.

290
00:13:35,919 --> 00:13:36,760
Why do you always have to

291
00:13:36,799 --> 00:13:38,200
spout so much nonsense first?

292
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:40,799
Alright.

293
00:13:41,599 --> 00:13:42,479
Well,

294
00:13:42,599 --> 00:13:44,159
the instructions from our head office,

295
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,000
have you heard about them?

296
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,119
They notified me.

297
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:49,960
They said I should rest for a year.

298
00:13:50,119 --> 00:13:51,799
They will reimburse all medical expenses,

299
00:13:51,799 --> 00:13:52,760
and provide a house and a car.

300
00:13:53,119 --> 00:13:54,719
A 24-hour heart specialist

301
00:13:54,719 --> 00:13:55,520
will be on call at all times.

302
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,919
And it's a paid leave.

303
00:13:57,359 --> 00:13:58,840
I am the most promising candidate

304
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,400
to become the next vice president.

305
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:01,880
Of course they would treat me like this.

306
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:06,400
Once we settle Feimanchi next week,

307
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,520
the career I've worked so hard for most of my life

308
00:14:09,039 --> 00:14:10,520
can temporarily come to a close.

309
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,960
So,

310
00:14:13,159 --> 00:14:15,119
you're following their arrangements?

311
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,119
Why not?

312
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:17,919
I've worked so hard,

313
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:19,520
and now my health is finally better.

314
00:14:20,239 --> 00:14:21,520
I want to start a new life.

315
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:24,479
Then when you go on vacation,

316
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,000
who will you arrange

317
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,679
to protect you and accompany you?

318
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,640
You already know.

319
00:14:30,479 --> 00:14:31,239
When the time comes,

320
00:14:31,679 --> 00:14:32,239
sunshine,

321
00:14:32,479 --> 00:14:33,080
beaches,

322
00:14:33,359 --> 00:14:34,559
and a big group of beauties.

323
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,400
I'll arrange them all for you.

324
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,679
I'm being discharged at noon tomorrow.

325
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:37,679
Don't be late.

326
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,320
If you don't choose me then,

327
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,080
I'll kill you.

328
00:14:43,039 --> 00:14:43,760
I heard you!

329
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,280
Looking for me as soon as you get back.

330
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,119
It must be nothing good.

331
00:15:01,679 --> 00:15:02,559
A new friend.

332
00:15:03,599 --> 00:15:04,039
Hello.

333
00:15:04,479 --> 00:15:05,919
I'm the legal director of Feimanchi,

334
00:15:06,039 --> 00:15:06,760
Feng Ziang.

335
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:08,880
The legal director of Feimanchi.

336
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,919
Is this what you call

337
00:15:20,359 --> 00:15:21,520
biting the hand that feeds you?

338
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,359
As for me,

339
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,880
I've stayed abroad for too long.

340
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,119
I'm not very good with idioms.

341
00:15:25,719 --> 00:15:26,559
If I said it wrong,

342
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:27,599
please don't mind.

343
00:15:30,719 --> 00:15:32,559
What can Rosenmoss Company give you?

344
00:15:33,239 --> 00:15:34,719
Money or job opportunities?

345
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,200
What if I say

346
00:15:36,559 --> 00:15:37,760
what I want is Feimanchi?

347
00:15:38,719 --> 00:15:39,599
Can you accept that?

348
00:15:40,719 --> 00:15:41,239
What did you say?

349
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,359
Nelson.

350
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,440
The CEO means that

351
00:15:45,679 --> 00:15:47,559
after pushing Director Feng to be the manager,

352
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,000
he will naturally become the acting CEO.

353
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,799
Do you think I won't live long,

354
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:52,880
so you don't need to tell me?

355
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:53,400
Right?

356
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,599
Nelson, what are you saying?

357
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,679
Anyway, after Feimanchi goes bankrupt,

358
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:58,840
we'll always need someone

359
00:15:58,840 --> 00:15:59,760
to follow our intentions

360
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:00,559
to clean up the mess, right?

361
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:03,760
Feimanchi might not go bankrupt

362
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:05,239
this month as originally planned.

363
00:16:07,559 --> 00:16:09,320
We've already made a lot of effort.

364
00:16:09,679 --> 00:16:10,239
Didn't you tell me

365
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,520
their capital chain was already broken?

366
00:16:12,359 --> 00:16:13,559
How long have I been gone?

367
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,559
And you've messed things up like this.

368
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,640
Don't worry about it right now.

369
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,719
We'll immediately send Director Feng

370
00:16:19,719 --> 00:16:21,200
over as a seconded director.

371
00:16:21,479 --> 00:16:22,200
Director Feng came here today

372
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,400
exactly for this matter.

373
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:24,880
Seconded director.

374
00:16:25,559 --> 00:16:26,400
What for?

375
00:16:26,679 --> 00:16:27,400
Nominally,

376
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,080
it's to oversee Feimanchi paying off its debts.

377
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,440
But in reality,

378
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,640
it's to make them quickly fall into financial trouble.

379
00:16:33,919 --> 00:16:35,679
So that you can rest well, Mr. Gu.

380
00:16:36,239 --> 00:16:36,880
It looks like

381
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:38,760
I'll have to work two extra jobs.

382
00:16:41,159 --> 00:16:42,039
You talk too much.

383
00:16:43,159 --> 00:16:44,159
Believe it or not, I won't just make you

384
00:16:44,159 --> 00:16:45,320
lose your job at Rosenmoss,

385
00:16:46,119 --> 00:16:48,039
but also make you a beaten dog at Feimanchi.

386
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:56,239
Didn't we agree to live together?

387
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,320
Why didn't you discuss it with me

388
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:58,520
before deciding to move out?

389
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,039
I can't just freeload off you forever.

390
00:17:01,719 --> 00:17:02,799
A call. Hold on a second.

391
00:17:05,959 --> 00:17:06,640
Hello, Gaoming.

392
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,239
What?

393
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:11,920
Okay.

394
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:12,800
I got it.

395
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:13,839
I'll head back right away.

396
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,479
Something came up at the station?

397
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:16,359
Yeah.

398
00:17:16,479 --> 00:17:17,280
I have to leave right now.

399
00:17:17,959 --> 00:17:18,880
As for this luggage, I...

400
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:19,640
It's fine.

401
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,479
You go ahead.

402
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:21,319
Jiaqi,

403
00:17:21,479 --> 00:17:22,680
how about calling Ziang

404
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:23,479
and asking him to come help you?

405
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:24,319
No need.

406
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,719
Don't bother him with everything.

407
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,479
I'm off, I'm off.

408
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,560
I'm really leaving now.

409
00:17:29,239 --> 00:17:30,040
Bye-bye.

410
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:48,280
Tiancheng

411
00:17:49,199 --> 00:17:50,400
Your mom and dad

412
00:17:51,319 --> 00:17:52,680
are truly outstanding people.

413
00:17:53,479 --> 00:17:54,800
They always stood by others

414
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:56,199
through thick and thin.

415
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,599
When you grow up,

416
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:00,239
you should learn from them.

417
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,640
I will always remember

418
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:04,760
that Dad

419
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,280
was the biggest fool

420
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,760
in the entire world.

421
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,359
So I swore

422
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,479
never to become a man like my father.

423
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,359
Just like my destiny.

424
00:18:18,119 --> 00:18:20,000
You did all those things.

425
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,920
If you have no evidence,

426
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,920
I'll see you in court.

427
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,520
The late chairman Gu Rongtao,

428
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,000
did he leave a will stating

429
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,079
that all of his shares

430
00:18:26,079 --> 00:18:27,520
would be gifted to his brother Gu Rongchen?

431
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:28,560
Yes.

432
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,439
After notarization by the notary office,

433
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,520
the will is valid.
